<%content_for :title do%>How It Works<%end%>
<h1>How It Works</h1>
<br>
<ul id="how_it_works_list" class="list-group">
	<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="list-group-item-heading hiw_list_heading">Create a pool</h4>
		Sign up and create your own major league baseball playoff pool.  During sign up you will be asked to pick a unique pool name.  This name will be used to identify your pool from others.  It is what your friends will use when they sign up.
	</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="list-group-item-heading hiw_list_heading">Invite your friends</h4>
		Let your friends, family, co-workers, etc know to sign up for your MLB playoff pool.  Give them the pool name you chose when you created the pool.  They need to use the pool name when they sign up.
	</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="list-group-item-heading hiw_list_heading">Make your picks</h4>
		Upon sign in, you will be taken directly to your personal MLB playoff bracket.  If the pairings are out for the playoffs, you can pick the winner of each series and save your bracket. The same applies to all players in your pool.
	</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="list-group-item-heading hiw_list_heading">Check the pool standings</h4>
		Once the MLB playoffs begin, standings and bracket results will be updated at the conclusion of each playoff series.  Check in frequently to see how you are doing against others in your playoff pool. 
	</li>
	<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="list-group-item-heading hiw_list_heading">Crown the winner!</h4>
		After the playoffs are complete check the point standings to determine the winner.  Shower them with glory and praise.
	</li>
</ul>
<br>
